PART II — SCALE RESTRICTION (applies when total users exceed 10,000)

1. THRESHOLD DEFINITION
   "Users" means the total number of distinct registered accounts
   created through or using this Software at any point in time,
   whether active, inactive, or deleted, counted cumulatively.

2. FREE TIER
   Use of this Software is granted free of charge for deployments
   serving fewer than ten thousand (10,000) users in total.

3. SCALE RESTRICTION
   Any deployment, product, service, or derivative work that reaches
   or exceeds ten thousand (10,000) total users MUST obtain prior
   written permission from the copyright holder before continuing
   to operate at or beyond that threshold.

4. HOW TO REQUEST PERMISSION
   To request permission for use beyond 10,000 users, contact the
   copyright holder at:

       GitHub:   github.com/Craftbuddy6317
       In-game:  Craftbuddy6317

   Requests must include:
   (a) The name and description of your deployment or product
   (b) Your estimated or current user count
   (c) Whether the use is commercial or non-commercial
   (d) Contact details for the requesting party

5. PERMISSION GRANTED
   Permission beyond the 10,000 user threshold may be granted or
   denied at the sole discretion of the copyright holder, with or
   without conditions, and with or without compensation.

6. VIOLATION
   Operating beyond the 10,000 user threshold without prior written
   permission from the copyright holder constitutes a breach of this
   license and automatically terminates all rights granted under
   Part I of this license.

